import numpy as np
from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn import metrics
import pandas as pd

class ParamsAndAccuracy:
    def __init__(self, layers, neurons, neuronRatio, batchSize, epochs, optimizer, activation, val_accuracy, accuracy):
        self.layers = layers
        self.neurons = neurons
        self.neuronRatio = neuronRatio
        self.batchSize = batchSize
        self.epochs = epochs
        self.optimizer = optimizer
        self.activation = activation
        self.val_accuracy = val_accuracy
        self.accuracy = accuracy
    
    def __str__(self):
        return ("Val_Accuracy: %f\nAccuracy: %f\nLayers: %d\nNeurons: %d\nNeuronRatio: %f\nBatchSize: %d\nEpochs: %d\nOptimizer: %s\nActivation: %s\n" % (self.val_accuracy, self.accuracy, self.layers, self.neurons, self.neuronRatio, self.batchSize, self.epochs, self.optimizer, self.activation))

class ModelData:
    
    dataset : np.ndarray
    XVALID : np.ndarray
    YVALID : np.ndarray
    XTRAIN : np.ndarray
    YTRAIN : np.ndarray
    model : Sequential
       
    layers = 0
    neurons = 0
    neuronRatio = 0
    batchSize = 0
    epochs = 0
    optimizer = 0
    activation = 0

    def getLayers(self):
        return self.layers
    def getNeurons(self):
        return self.neurons
    def getNeuronRatio(self):
        return self.neuronRatio
    def getBatchSize(self):
        return self.batchSize
    def getEpochs(self):
        return self.epochs
    def getOptimizer(self):
        return self.optimizer
    def getActivation(self):
        return self.activation
    
    
    def setHyperParameters(self, layers, neurons, neuronRatio, batchSize, epochs, optimizer, activation):
        self.layers = layers
        self.neurons = neurons
        self.neuronRatio = neuronRatio
        self.batchSize = batchSize
        self.epochs = epochs
        self.optimizer = optimizer
        self.activation = activation
    
    def __init__(self, dataset):
        self.dataset = dataset
        self.setData()
        
    def setData(self, printShape = False):
        np.random.shuffle(self.dataset)

        idx = int(0.3 * len(self.dataset[:, 0]))
        
        self.XVALID = self.dataset[:idx, range(len(dataset[0]) - 1)]
        self.YVALID = self.dataset[:idx, [len(dataset[0]) - 1]]
        self.XTRAIN = self.dataset[idx:, range(len(dataset[0]) - 1)]
        self.YTRAIN = self.dataset[idx:, [len(dataset[0]) - 1]]
        
        # normalize
        mean = self.XTRAIN.mean(axis=0)
        self.XTRAIN -= mean
        std = self.XTRAIN.std(axis=0)
        self.XTRAIN /= std
        
        self.XVALID -= mean
        self.XVALID /= std
        
        if (printShape):
            print(self.XVALID.shape)
            print(self.YVALID.shape)
            print(self.XTRAIN.shape)
            print(self.YTRAIN.shape)
        
    def setModel(self, printSummary = False, isSingleLayer = False, setLastLayer=False):
        self.model = Sequential()
    
        neuronCount = self.getNeurons()
        if (isSingleLayer):
            self.model.add(Dense(1, input_dim = len(self.XTRAIN[0, :]), activation="sigmoid"))
        else:
            self.model.add(Dense(neuronCount, input_dim = len(self.XTRAIN[0, :]), activation=self.getActivation()))
            for i in range(self.getLayers() - 2):
                neuronCount -= neuronCount * self.getNeuronRatio()
                self.model.add(Dense(neuronCount, activation=self.getActivation()))
            self.model.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))

        self.model.compile(loss = 'BinaryCrossentropy', optimizer = self.getOptimizer(), metrics=['accuracy'])
        
        if (printSummary):
            print(self.model.summary())
            
    
    def run(self, verbose = 0, showPlots = False, outputImageTag=""):
    
        history = self.model.fit(self.XTRAIN, self.YTRAIN, validation_data = (self.XVALID, self.YVALID), batch_size = self.getBatchSize(), epochs = self.getEpochs(), verbose = verbose)
        
        paramsAndAccuracy = ParamsAndAccuracy(self.getLayers(), self.getNeurons(), self.getNeuronRatio(), self.getBatchSize(), self.getEpochs(), self.getOptimizer(), self.getActivation(), history.history['val_accuracy'][-1], history.history['accuracy'][-1])
        
        if (showPlots):
            y_pred = self.model.predict(self.XVALID)
            y_pred_rounded = y_pred.round()
            fpr, tpr, _ = metrics.roc_curve(self.YVALID, y_pred)

            m = [[metrics.accuracy_score(self.YVALID, y_pred_rounded), metrics.log_loss(self.YVALID, y_pred), metrics.precision_score(self.YVALID, y_pred_rounded), metrics.recall_score(self.YVALID, y_pred_rounded), metrics.f1_score(self.YVALID, y_pred_rounded), metrics.auc(fpr, tpr)]]
            df_metrics = pd.DataFrame(m, columns=["Accuracy", "Loss", "Precision", "Recall", "F1 Score", "AUC"])

            tableOutputFile = open("metricsOutput.txt", "a")
            tableOutputFile.write(df_metrics.style.to_latex(index=False))
            tableOutputFile.write("\n")
            tableOutputFile.close()
            print(df_metrics)

            plotFileName = "plt"

            print(history.params)
            plt.plot(history.history['loss'])
            plt.plot(history.history['val_loss'])
            plt.ylabel('loss')
            plt.xlabel('epoch')
            plt.legend(['training data', 'validation data'], loc='upper center')
            plt.savefig("%sLoss%s.png" % (plotFileName, outputImageTag))
            plt.show()
            
            plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'])
            plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'])
            plt.ylabel('accuracy')
            plt.xlabel('epoch')
            plt.legend(['training data', 'validation data'], loc='lower right')
            plt.savefig("%sAcc%s.png" % (plotFileName, outputImageTag))
            plt.show()

            fpr, tpr, _ = metrics.roc_curve(self.YVALID, y_pred)
            plt.plot(fpr, tpr)
            plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], linestyle='--')
            plt.xlim([0.0, 1.0])
            plt.ylim([0.0, 1.0])
            plt.xlabel('specificity')
            plt.ylabel('sensitivity')
            plt.savefig("%sROC%s.png" % (plotFileName, outputImageTag))
            plt.show()
        
        return paramsAndAccuracy

mData.setHyperParameters(layers, neurons, neuronRatio, batchSize, epochs, optimizer, activation)
mData.setModel(printSummary=True, isSingleLayer=True)
mData.run(verbose=1, showPlots=True)
